# Planner — Improve Pass 2

## Change scope

Audio asset swap only. All UI, Web Audio engine architecture, mixer/solo/mute/pan/loop/seek, section nav, count-in, cue overlay, and Scheduler remain untouched.

Affected files (minimal):
1. `demo-src/src/engine/AudioEngine.js` — remove 200 lines of synth helpers + render functions; replace `loadSong()` to fetch real stem files and decode via `decodeAudioData()`
2. `demo-src/src/data/songs.js` — replace 3 fake songs with real Tommy Walker song metadata; remove `ROOT_HZ`; update `STEM_CONFIG` labels/icons to match real stem names
3. `demo-src/public/audio/<slug>/` (3 new dirs) — 6 compressed MP3 stems each (~128-192 kbps), placed so Vite serves them statically
4. Rebuild + copy dist to `../michaelwegter.com/public/demos/audio-software-engineer-needed-for/`
5. Git commit + push (michaelwegter.com only; mw-backend unaffected)

No media capture or proposal writer re-run needed (user's explicit instruction).

---

## AudioEngine.js refactor (key logic change)

Current `loadSong()` calls six async render functions that produce short loop buffers. Replace with:

```js
async loadSong(song, onProgress) {
  this._ensureContext();
  this.stop();
  this.song = song;
  this.stems = {};
  this.pauseOffset = 0;

  const stemEntries = Object.entries(song.stems); // { id: 'filename.mp3' }
  let done = 0;
  for (const [id, filename] of stemEntries) {
    const resp = await fetch(`audio/${song.slug}/${filename}`);
    const arrayBuf = await resp.arrayBuffer();
    const buf = await this.ctx.decodeAudioData(arrayBuf);
    const volumeGain = this.ctx.createGain();
    const muteGain = this.ctx.createGain();
    const panner = this.ctx.createStereoPanner();
    volumeGain.gain.value = 1.0;
    muteGain.gain.value = 1.0;
    panner.pan.value = 0;
    volumeGain.connect(panner);
    panner.connect(muteGain);
    muteGain.connect(this.masterGain);
    this.stems[id] = { buffer: buf, source: null, volumeGain, muteGain, panner,
                       volume: 80, muted: false, soloed: false, pan: 0 };
    done++;
    if (onProgress) onProgress(done / stemEntries.length);
  }
  this.totalDuration = Object.values(this.stems)[0].buffer.duration;
  return this.stems;
}
```

Keep `countIn()` (it still uses synth click ticks via OfflineAudioContext — preserve `schedClickTick` only).
Remove all other synth helpers and render functions.

`_createSources()` stays unchanged — `src.loop = true` with `loopEnd = stem.buffer.duration` means songs auto-repeat if listener leaves it running (fine for demo purposes).

