## songs.js schema addition

Add `stems` field (map of stem ID to filename) to each song:

```js
{
  id: 1,
  slug: 'song-slug',       // used in fetch path: audio/song-slug/filename.mp3
  title: 'Real Song Title',
  artist: 'Tommy Walker',
  key: 'A',
  bpm: 75,
  timeSignature: [4, 4],
  totalDuration: 245,      // actual seconds from decoded buffer (also update this)
  sections: [...],         // real section timestamps from chart/liner notes
  cues: [...],             // real lyric/section cues
  stems: {
    drums:  '01_Drums.mp3',
    bass:   '02_Bass.mp3',
    keys:   '03_Keys.mp3',
    pads:   '04_Pads.mp3',
    click:  '05_Click.mp3',
    guide:  '06_Guide.mp3',
  }
}
```

Remove `synthKey`, `barDuration`, `loopDuration` from all songs (no longer needed).
Remove `ROOT_HZ` export.
Update `STEM_CONFIG` labels/icons to match real stem content (e.g. guide -> "Guide Vox").

---

## File placement

```
demo-src/public/audio/
  <slug1>/  01_Drums.mp3  02_Bass.mp3  03_Keys.mp3  04_Pads.mp3  05_Click.mp3  06_Guide.mp3
  <slug2>/  ...
  <slug3>/  ...
```

Vite includes everything in `public/` verbatim in the build. After `npm run build`, these appear at `/demos/audio-software-engineer-needed-for/audio/<slug>/filename.mp3`.

Target total bundle: each stem ~2-4 MB at 128 kbps for a 3-5 min song. 6 stems x 3 songs = 18 files. Goal: keep each song under 20 MB total (transcode to 128 kbps if source is WAV or high-bitrate MP3).

---

## Research questions for pre-researcher

The following must be resolved before demo-builder can act:

1. **Song catalog** — Log in to https://www.tommywalkerministries.org/multitracksmenu (name: michael wegter, email: zweetztuph@gmail.com, uncheck "receive emails"). List all available song titles with stem packages.

2. **Song selection** — Identify 3 songs suitable for a live worship band demo: mix of tempos (one slow ballad, one mid-tempo, one uptempo). For each, report:
   - Exact title
   - BPM (from package notes or click track if audible)
   - Key
   - Runtime (total seconds)
   - Available stem file names and formats in the download package

3. **Stem inventory** — For each of the 3 chosen songs, list every file in the download package. Confirm which files map to: drums, bass, keys/piano, pads/atmospheres, click/metronome, guide/reference vocals. Note any stems that don't fit (e.g. acoustic guitar, electric guitar) — we'll decide whether to add them to STEM_CONFIG or omit.

4. **Section timestamps** — For each song, list named sections (intro, verse, pre-chorus, chorus, bridge, outro) with approximate start times in seconds. Source: PDF chart in the package, audio waveform cues, or known Tommy Walker song structure.

5. **Download + transcode** — Download the 3 stem packages. If WAV or high-bitrate, transcode to MP3 128 kbps stereo. Report final file sizes. Place transcoded stems in `demo-src/public/audio/<slug>/` (use kebab-case slug derived from song title).

6. **File path confirmation** — Report the exact relative paths of all 18 audio files placed (so demo-builder can wire `songs.stems` directly).

If any song's stem package is missing a critical stem (drums or guide vocals), pick a different song.

---

## Plan status

**READY FOR PRE-RESEARCHER.** Architecture and change scope are fully defined. Blocked on: song selection, stem file names, BPM/key/duration, section timestamps, and actual downloaded+transcoded files. Pre-researcher resolves all 6 questions above; demo-builder then executes with no remaining unknowns.

